name: Bokujust
description:
####################################################

This is a merged model created to reflect my preferences.

At the time of posting, there are 4 models.

####################################################

My models are NOT specialized in sumi-e, ink painting and some bokujuu painting art.

Bokuju is just my username.

####################################################

  • BokuRough: emphasis on analog feel, roughness and vivid colors

  • BokuSoft: softness, lighting, and simple screens

  • Bokujust V1.0a: an equally merging model of BokuRough and BokuSoft, well-balanced

  • Bokujust V1.0b: a merging model of BokuRough and BokuSoft with block weight, MY TASTE

####################################################

Recommended Settings

  • CFG: 5 to 9

  • Sampler: Any

  • Steps: 20 to 40

  • Hires Steps: Half of Step, but more than 10

  • Upscaler: Any

  • VAE: Any

  • Embedding: I don't recommend use it. Or apply it WEAKLY. It improves the quality but unique properties of the model will be destroyed.

####################################################

Questions are welcome.

####################################################

Bokuju

modelVersions.name: Bokujust V1.0b
modelVersions.description:
This is a finished model.

This model is created by merging BokuRough and BokuSoft with block weight.

The features and strengths of each are emphasized more than Bokujust V1.0a.

The lighting and reflections are beautifully done.

The finish is a bit quirky, but it is strongly ”””IN LINE WITH MY TASTE”””.
